**** {{topt|Will you pack your things now?}}
***** '''Player:''' Will you pack your things now?
***** '''Trufitus:''' I will wait and see what will happen. Maybe Rashiliyia does not have the power to strike too far from her resting place? But there are many things that I need to do now.
***** {{topt|Is her resting place important?}}
****** '''Player:''' Is her resting place important?
****** '''Trufitus:''' I believe it is! It might be that her physical remains are the focal point of her supernatural powers. It is said that many years ago, a group of adventurers once infiltrated her tomb to try to rid the world of Rashiliyia.
****** '''Trufitus:''' These adventurers reported seeing a wraith- like creature.
****** '''Trufitus:''' Although the adventurers disturbed Rashiliyia's bones, they were not able to properly sanctify them. And this is the most likely reason why she still plagues us today.
****** '''Trufitus:''' Of course, she only has to order one of her minions to move her bones and she can quite quickly and easily set up a new headquarters anywhere and continue to launch her plague of undead.
****** {{topt|What are minions?}}
******* '''Player:''' What are minions?
******* '''Trufitus:''' Minions are the fiendish undead creatures that she controls. She has very few living worshippers, but they need to be dealt with at some point.
******* {{topt|Thanks for the information!}}
******** {{tact|above}}
